    "historicalContext": "The Singleton Colony at Dunlap represents the Exoduster movement, a significant migration of African Americans from the South to Kansas in the late 19th century. This movement was driven by the desire to escape racial oppression and establish independent Black communities. The colony's cemetery, established in 1880, reflects the racial segregation and the need for Black communities to create their own spaces for burial and remembrance."
